## `<file-level: overview>`
<!-- checksum: rust-perms-1 -->

### Purpose
Pure permission-check logic: given a node's `(mode, uid, gid)`, the caller's `(uid, gid)`, and a requested `Access` mask, decide whether access is granted. Mirrors Linux kernel `generic_permission()` semantics. Module is stateless — no struct, no Connection.

### Implementation Notes

```rust
use crate::errors::{Error, Result};
use crate::types::Access;
```

---

## `pub fn check_access(node_mode, node_uid, node_gid, caller_uid, caller_gid, access) -> bool`
<!-- checksum: rust-perms-2 -->

### Purpose
Pure predicate. Returns `true` iff the caller is permitted the requested access. Never errors — `require_access` is the raising wrapper.

### Preconditions
- `node_mode` masked to `[0, 0o7777]` by caller convention (lowest 12 bits relevant).
- `access` is an `Access` flag combination (`R`, `W`, `X`, or any OR thereof).

### Postconditions
- Returns `true` iff the caller holds every requested bit:
  - If `caller_uid == 0` (root):
    - For `R` and `W`: always granted.
    - For `X`: granted iff at least one execute bit is set anywhere in mode (owner/group/other). Matches `generic_permission()`'s `MAY_EXEC` rule for root.
  - Else if `caller_uid == node_uid`: use owner bits `(mode >> 6) & 0o7`.
  - Else if `caller_gid == node_gid`: use group bits `(mode >> 3) & 0o7`.
  - Else: use other bits `mode & 0o7`.
  - Combined access (e.g., `R | W`): every requested bit must be present in the selected triple.

### Invariants
Pure function; deterministic; no I/O.

### Implementation Notes

```rust
pub fn check_access(
    node_mode: u32, node_uid: u32, node_gid: u32,
    caller_uid: u32, caller_gid: u32,
    access: Access,
) -> bool {
    // Root bypass — conditional on execute.
    if caller_uid == 0 {
        if access.contains(Access::X) {
            let any_x = (node_mode & 0o111) != 0;
            if !any_x { return false; }
        }
        return true;  // root: R/W always; X already validated above
    }

    // Non-root: select the appropriate triple.
    let bits: u32 = if caller_uid == node_uid {
        (node_mode >> 6) & 0o7
    } else if caller_gid == node_gid {
        (node_mode >> 3) & 0o7
    } else {
        node_mode & 0o7
    };

    let required = access.bits();
    (bits & required) == required
}
```

### Failure Modes
None.

---

## `pub fn require_access(...) -> Result<()>`
<!-- checksum: rust-perms-3 -->

### Purpose
Raising wrapper. Returns `Ok(())` when access is granted, `Err(Error::PermissionDenied(...))` otherwise. Called from `fs.rs` at every op site that needs to enforce permissions.

### Implementation Notes

```rust
pub fn require_access(
    node_mode: u32, node_uid: u32, node_gid: u32,
    caller_uid: u32, caller_gid: u32,
    access: Access,
) -> Result<()> {
    if check_access(node_mode, node_uid, node_gid, caller_uid, caller_gid, access) {
        Ok(())
    } else {
        Err(Error::PermissionDenied(format!(
            "access {access:?} denied: caller=({caller_uid},{caller_gid}), \
             node=({node_uid},{node_gid},0o{node_mode:o})"
        )))
    }
}
```

### Failure Modes
- `Error::PermissionDenied` if access is not granted. **propagated**.

